%N A387053 a(n) is the least k such that n is the sum of a prime and k powers of 2.
%H A387053 David A. Corneth, <a href="/A387053/b387053.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 2..10001</a>
%H A387053 Thomas Bloom, <a href="https://www.erdosproblems.com/10">Problem 10</a>, Erd≈ës Problems.
%F A387053 a(n) = 0 <=> n is prime.
%e A387053 a(4) = 1 as 4 is the sum of a prime (2) and one power of 2 (2) but 4 is not prime.
%t A387053 a[n_]:=Module[{res},If[PrimeQ[n],Return[0]];res=Min[Map[DigitCount[n - #, 2, 1]&,Select[Range[2,n],PrimeQ]]];res];Array[a,96,2] (* _James C. McMahon_, Sep 23 2025 *)
%o A387053 (PARI) a(n) = if(isprime(n),return(0)); my(res=oo); forprime(p=2, n, res = min(res, hammingweight(n-p))); res
%o A387053 (Python)
%o A387053 from sympy import isprime, primerange
%o A387053 def a(n): return 0 if isprime(n) else min((n-p).bit_count() for p in primerange(1, n))
